    The classic Stroop task measuring color-word interference effects.
    Participants name the ink color of color words, which may be congruent
    (word RED in red ink) or incongruent (word RED in blue ink).
  `,

  parameters: {
    practiceTrials: {
      type: 'number',
      default: 10,
      min: 0,
      max: 50,
      description: 'Number of practice trials before main experiment'
    },

    testTrials: {
      type: 'number', 
